nchise-specific, and big-budget comedy is now dominating the box office. La=
st summer, <i>Barbie</i> earned $1.4 billion worldwide, displacing that sam=
e year=E2=80=99s <i>The Super Mario Bros. Movie </i>($1.3 billion) as the t=
op-earning comedy of all time. <i>Inside Out 2 </i>just topped $1.5 billion=
 worldwide, and now <i>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine </i>might make a play for t=
he gold. Those hits join <i>Despicable Me 4 </i>(likely to end with around =
$800 million), <i>Wonka </i>($615 million), <i>Bad Boys: Ride or Die </i>($=
395 million and counting),
<i>Mean Girls </i>($105 million) and <i>Kung Fu Panda 4</i> ($545 million) =
as franchise films that prioritize comedy over action and spectacle. The po=
int: Comedy didn=E2=80=99t die, it was just supersized. =E2=80=94<i>Scott M=
endelson</i><br/><br/><i>Now for tip-off on the main event=E2=80=A6.</i><br=
/></td>
